- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the numerical stability and robustness of computations against roundoff errors, which are important topics in numerical analysis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper's focus on Kalman filtering and likelihood evaluation may be relevant to certain applications in AI, such as tracking and prediction. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may be of interest to software engineers who work on implementing Kalman filtering algorithms and need to ensure numerical stability and robustness.
